cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper deals with Monte Carlo sampling methods for high-dimensional nonisotropic distributions, which are commonly encountered in machine learning and optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses applications in optimization, which suggests the possibility of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as additional sub-categories.
